      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's getting better, but the score is still stagnant. the tool is barely registering any new 'features' because most of what you're adding is just rephrasing the same specs. \n\nlook, i know i said not to pad it, but if we don't get that feature count up, this article is basically invisible to the algorithm. you need to find more granular details to talk about. even if it's something small—like the specific tech behind the screen, the exact type of charging, or even breaking down the dimensions or weight if you can infer them—just maximize the amount of unique feature points you can identify and compare. the more individual specs you can pull out and label as a 'feature', the better the score will be. try one more time and really go deep into every single aspect possible.",
